<br>
1. I'll also point to snare-kiting as a viable, standard party.<br>
<br>
2. I actually find all-pet groups relatively hard to form, especially compared to snare groups. In large part because the all pet group has to completely reject all meele classes, a harsh restriction. Pet classes are also relatively uncommon, and because mage dps is entirely respectable, relatively competed over.<br>
<br>
3. I have yet to see a single party doable mob that, if slowed, single-pulled, my pet buffed, and we have a cleric, that my epic pet can't tank. Hell, well-equipped shaman's can usually tank slowed 500 hitters.<br>
<br>
4. If you only have one pet and no meeles, then what you are basically describing is a &quot;holy trinity&quot; group, with the mage functioning as the tank.<br>
<br>
5. I think holy trinity might not be the right word to use. In the past, what holy trinity meant to me was there were three classes (enchanter, cleric, (depends-who-you-ask; rogue/warrior)) that were considered essential in any group AND irreplacable. You had to have a cleric; other healers wouldn't cut it; you had to have an enchanter, other mezzers didn't work. These days the classic group might have three important roles, but many classes can fill the roles. Tank (warrior, SK, paladin, mage, charmed pet, maybe beastlord, monk), healer (cleric, druid, shaman), slower (shaman, enchanter, sorta beastlord or bard). Each role has several possible ways to fill it; and the tank role is especially diverse. Furthermore, since druids are a relatively common class, the healer role is not too hard to fill. In raiding guilds clerics are relatively common as well. The problem with the slower role, in my experience, is that the classes that can fill that role are currently uncommon. So this makes slowers seem like a &quot;god&quot; class. Maybe necro/shadowknight slows should be improved a bit?<br>
<br>
6. In the classic group there is also a spot for the &quot;damage role&quot; and rogues, mages, (and charmed pets) are the kings of sustained DPS. I have not had any problems being frozen out of groups.<br>
<br>
